<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Nazgul Minions<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.20)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10558'>Ulaire "Morgul Minas" Lemenya</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10558&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> April 27, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Nazgul have a lot of minions to choose from and are the only culture that have two versions of the one minion. You can&#39;t possible just put 4 x each Ringwraith and 4x Bill Ferny into each deck. Thus you have some real choices to make. <br />
<br />
First lets look at the minions and see what they do. <br />
<br />
Bill Ferny, Swarthy Sneering Fellow R 2<br />
Minion Man. Nazgûl are not roaming. The Free Peoples player<br />
may not assign a character to skirmish Bill Ferny. Discard Bill Ferny if underground. 4/1/2 <br />
<br />
People seem very excited by this minion as they see him as a great chance to overwhelm. Yet at strength 4 how much better is he than an event like Threshold of Shadow which people can&#39;t even see coming? I rate him as OK.<br />
<br />
Ulaire Attea, Keeper of Dol Guldur R 6<br />
Minion Nazgul. Fierce. Skirmish: Remove 1<br />
to make Ulaire Attea strength +1 (limit +5). 12/3/3<br />
or <br />
Ulaire Attea, The Easterling U 6<br />
Minion Nazgûl. Twilight. When you play Úlairë Attëa, you may<br />
wound an ally. 12/3/3<br />
<br />
The first version is a tank who is a good chance to overwhelm an opponent. However Nazgul always seem to have a shortage of twylight anyway and wouldn&#39;t you rather play another Nazgul? The second one has a great ability. Make Bounder useless. Probably kill the Gaffer or Farmer Maggot. Make Tharin useless. Possibly kill Elrond or Galadriel. The possiblitiies are endless. Unfortunatly The Easterling is not fierce, a big disadvantage. A very tough choice but I might just go with the Keeper of Dol Guldur. <br />
<br />
Ulaire Cantea, Lieutenant of Dol Guldur R 5<br />
Minion Nazgul. Fierce. Skirmish: Exert Ulaire‚<br />
Cantea to discard a weapon borne by a<br />
character he is skirmishing. 10/3/3<br />
<br />
This is possibly the best Nazgûl now with the huge amount of FLaming Brands that you will see. He is a must. I would use 4 of him in a deck if I owened 4.<br />
<br />
Ulaire Enquea, Lieutenant of Morgul U 6<br />
Minion Nazgul. Fierce. Maneuver: Spot 6<br />
companions (or 5 burdens) and exert Ulaire<br />
Enquea to wound a companion (except the Ring-<br />
bearer). 11/4/3<br />
or<br />
Ulaire Enquea, Ringwraith in Twilight U 6<br />
Minion Nazgûl. Twilight. Each time Úlairë Enquëa wins a<br />
skirmish, you may exert him to wound the Ring-bearer once (or twice if you spot 5 burdens). 11/4/3<br />
<br />
While the Ringwraith in Twilight is nice I think the Lieutenant of Morgul is much better. This is one of the cards that really punish large fellowships. If your opponent knows you have him the will not go above 5 companions. Such a useful text that he can even be used in non-Nazgul decks. I would have at least 2 in every Nazgul deck.<br />
<br />
Ulaire Lemenya, Lieutenant of Morgul U 4<br />
Minion Nazgul. Each companion or ally who<br />
bears a Nazgul condition is strength -2. 9/2/3<br />
<br />
Not very good (how can I say that?) by himself but with his sword he is really good. His main other virtue is that he is cheap for a Nazgûl. Many people don&#39;t use him but he does fit into some decks.<br />
<br />
Ulaire Nelya, Lieutenant of Morgul U 5<br />
Minion Nazgul. Fierce. Shadow: Exert Ulaire‚<br />
Nelya and spot an opponent&#39;s site to replace it<br />
with your site of the same number. 10/3/2<br />
or<br />
Ulaire Nelya, Ringwraith in Twilight R 5<br />
Minion Nazgûl. Twilight. While you can spot 2 burdens or 2<br />
wounds on the Ring-bearer, Úlairë Nelya is fierce and damage +1. 10/3/2<br />
<br />
This is a really tough choice as both of these are fantastic. What Nazgul deck doesn&#39;t have at least 2 of Nelya in it? The Lieutenant of Morgul has fantastic game text being able to replace sites - great to ensure you get the Ford of Bruinen or any other crucial site. In fact this text is so good that you sometimes see him in non-Nazgul decks as well. Something to consider if a site is vital to you. The <br />
Ringwraith in Twilight is great with damage +1 but with the prevalence of armour these days perhaps the Lieutenant of Morgul still wins.<br />
<br />
Ulaire Nertea, Messenger of Dol Guldur U 4<br />
Minion Nazgul. When you play Ulaire Nertea,<br />
for each companion over 4, you may play 1<br />
minion from your discard pile. 9/2/3<br />
<br />
While not so tough in battle this text is also great. Five (or 4) is probably the most common number of companions and this lets you get out and re-use whichever minion would be the best in the situation. A couple of him should probably go in every deck. He is also useful in non-Nazgûl decks for players that don&#39;t have all of the rares that they want. Imagine that you are playing Uruks and only have one Lurtz and no Captains. How can you re-use Lurtz? With a Nertea!<br />
<br />
Ulaire Ostea, Lieutenant of Morgul U 4<br />
Minion Nazgul. Shadow: Exert Ulaire Ostea to<br />
make a Nazgul minion fierce. 9/3/3<br />
<br />
Great game text. Don&#39;t forget that he can make himself fierce and then make another Nazgul fierce as well. He is also cheap for a Nazgul and so probably belongs in all Nazgûl decks.<br />
<br />
Ulaire Toldea, Messenger of Morgul R 6<br />
Minion Nazgul. Fierce. Assignment: Spot 4<br />
burdens to assign a companion (except the Ring-<br />
bearer) to skirmish Ulaire Toldea. 12/3/3<br />
<br />
In a burden deck he is a one man wrecking team. Often you can find somone you can overwhelm and you will never have to face those annoying brands. If you don&#39;t have any way to assign burdens he is less good but at STR 12 and fierce he is hard to leave out.<br />
 <br />
The Witch-king, Lord of Angmar R 8<br />
Minion Nazgul. Fierce. For each other Nazgul<br />
you can spot, The Witch-king is strength +2. 14/4/3<br />
or<br />
The Witch-king, Lord of the Nazgûl R 8<br />
Minion Nazgûl. Twilight. Return to Its Master may not be played. Each time The Witch-king wins a skirmish, you may exert him to wound the Ring-bearer twice. 14/4/3<br />
<br />
He is the biggest and baddest and whichever version you use you will not be sorry. Lord of Angmar is an overwhelm machine and coupled with the Pale Blade will really make your opponents cry. The Lord of the Nazgûl is also fantastic, one of the best cards for putting Frodo under pressure. A must in a twylight burden deck. For normal gameplay I would probably stick with the Lord of Angmar but it is a close call.<br />
<br />
Ok, we have looked at all of the cards now we must construct our deck. We will assume we have 10-15 non-minion cards in our shadow half of the deck and so will have about 20 card spaces for minions. What do we put in? My suggestion would be something like...<br />
<br />
Ulaire Attea, Keeper of Dol Guldur x2<br />
Ulaire Cantea, Lieutenant of Dol Guldur x4<br />
Ulaire Enquea, Lieutenant of Morgul x2<br />
Ulaire Lemenya, Lieutenant of Morgul <br />
Ulaire Nelya, Lieutenant of Morgul x3<br />
Ulaire Nertea, Messenger of Dol Guldur x2<br />
Ulaire Ostea, Lieutenant of Morgul <br />
Ulaire Toldea, Messenger of Morgul x2<br />
The Witch-king, Lord of Angmar x3<br />
<br />
If you were playing a twylight burden deck your choices would naturally be different. I have also tried to have a good variety of Nazgul as there is nothing worse than having three of the same Nazgul in your hand. <br />
<br />
I am sure a lot of people will greatly disagree with this and I am keen to read your helpful feedback.<br />
<br />
Now go and find the ring. <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?id=3626&view=1&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
